<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Benezetta PiaAdiuvo on 05-02-2001 02:37 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I was recently sitting in the zone canyon in OverThere...the nice long one that leads to FM.  A dr00d was having a high old time kiting up and down there, irregardless of the fact that he was a)training the groups who were medding at either end of the canyon, and b)training the poor souls entering OT after a hazardous trip through FM, often near dead.

Tiring of such foolishness, as well as res'ing the poor souls he killed, I politely sent him a tell and asked him to find another place to kite, and what his actions were doing to innocent players.  My mode of thinking being, if he wanted to kite, he should do so in a place where he at least accepted a LITTLE of the risk that goes with it.  However, my suggestion was rather rudely received, to put it mildly.

So I plopped my little High Elvish butt right down in the OT canyon.  The next time I saw him up to his tricks, I Enstilled his sarnak knights.  I then Atoned them, and proceeded to nonchalantly nuke the daylights out of them.  It was rather fun, and I encouraged another cleric and chanter friend to join in the fray...amazin' what we'll do when bored, isn't it?

Needless to say, a_pissed_off_dr00d_01 started accusing me of KS'ing.  Me, a noble cleric?  Naw...."d00d, you were running towards a zone with mobs on you.  Looked like you needed help, so I gave it. I sure didn't want you to die. (snicker)  And I'll keep on giving it, as long as I see any mobs running after a player in this canyon."

He did try the trick one more time.  This time I let him get the mob just a smidge away from dying, then it got mem blurred and retributioned until it went to meet it's maker.  

Apparently he tired of wasting his mana for no good reason, and left the area.  Some people will never learn; just because they have the capability of doing something, does NOT give them the right to endanger others.
I still laugh about this, btw.



------------------
Benezetta Pia`Adiuvo
Tunarian Priestess of 44 Prayers
Paradise Lost / Xegony</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
